Articles.Content:
I've tried installing KSP on my rig.

Phenom X6 3.2GHz

16 Gig Ram

Radeon R7

64-bit Windows 10

Both the installer and the Zip package for 1.0.5 (downloaded Via the Squad store) show corrupt file markers when they get to the parts containers. Installation and unzipping will not continue in both cases. Any1 else experienced this?

Hmm... I know there is an ongoing issue with the KSP installer but I have heard nothing about the zip files having an issue.

Make sure you are installing to a clean non-windows indext folder.   Use the latest winRar to unpack is my recommendation that way you will have an error log to post if it fails again.  

WINRAR

tried multiple times over the last 2 days. MS Edge, and Firefox so I don't think its a browser issue.
Both the launcher and the zip show CRC errors.

Interestingly enough the game is still playable, however all 1.0.5 functions and parts are removed from game play......

I just tested the Windows store download and it seems to be fine.
